      arc: 'St John moves from apparent saviour — he rescues Jane from starvation — to a figure of subtle oppression. His proposal reveals the tyranny that can lurk within religious duty. He departs for India and, the novel implies, is approaching death at the close. His trajectory serves as a counterpoint to Jane and Rochester\'s earthly happiness.',
