      arc: 'Mrs Reed appears in two key moments: the opening chapters and a later deathbed scene (Chapter 21). Her refusal to repent or reconcile, even when dying, reveals the depth of her resentment and the moral bankruptcy of her position. She serves as a foil to Jane, whose capacity for forgiveness contrasts with Mrs Reed\'s implacable hatred.',
