          analysis:
            'Helen locates friendship — and identity — in the conscience rather than in social approval. This idea becomes foundational for Jane: when she faces the temptation to stay with Rochester, it is her conscience that compels her to leave. Helen teaches Jane that moral integrity is its own companionship.',
