          quote: 'By dying young, I shall escape great sufferings. I had not qualities or talents to make my way very well in the world: I should have been continually at fault.',
          chapter: 9,
          context: 'Facing her own death with calm acceptance.',
          analysis:
            'Helen\'s acceptance of death is both moving and troubling. Her self-deprecation — "I had not qualities" — may reflect genuine humility or the internalised criticism of teachers who punished her for dreaminess. Brontë leaves the reader to decide whether Helen\'s resignation is wisdom or defeat.',
