      arc: 'Adèle\'s arc is minor but significant. Under Jane\'s care, she develops from a spoiled child into a "pleasing and obliging companion." Her trajectory offers an optimistic counterpoint to Jane\'s own harsh childhood: with love and patience, children can flourish. Adèle\'s presence at Thornfield also provides a domestic context for Jane\'s relationship with Rochester, grounding their intellectual and emotional bond in the practical realities of daily life.',
