      arc: 'Brocklehurst is a relatively static character. He appears at Gateshead to interview Jane, then at Lowood to enforce his regime of deprivation. After the typhus epidemic exposes his mismanagement, he is stripped of sole authority over the school but retains his position as treasurer. His lack of reform or self-awareness makes him a figure of satirical condemnation rather than psychological complexity.',
